main event: The observer reported seeing two objects that appeared to be satellites in Washington, D.C. on January 13, 1957.
interesting points: The objects were described as the size of a half dollar at arm's length,The sighting lasted for two hours and fifteen minutes,The conclusion suggested the sighting was likely caused by weather balloons, satellites, aircraft, or astronomical phenomena,The sighting occurred at 2100 hours,The report was part of Project Blue Book which documented UFO sightings.
sighted object: two objects appearing to be satellites
